  "prompt": "What are big v telecoms consumer complaint and reviews?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the specific complaints and reviews regarding Big V Telecom (or any similar telecom provider) can vary widely based on customer experiences. Here are some common themes often found in consumer complaints and reviews regarding telecom services:\n\n1. **Customer Service**: Many consumers express frustration with long wait times, difficulty reaching support, unhelpful representatives, or lack of follow-up on issues.\n\n2. **Billing Issues**: Complaints about billing errors, unexpected charges, difficulties in understanding bills, and issues with payment processing are common.\n\n3. **Service Reliability**: Customers often voice concerns about dropped calls, slow internet speeds, or outages in service, affecting their overall experience.\n\n4. **Contract Terms and Changes**: Some reviews mention dissatisfaction with contract terms, such as fees for early termination or changes in rates after a promotional period ends.\n\n5. **Installation and Setup Problems**: Delays in installation, problems with equipment (such as routers or modems), and confusing setup processes can lead to negative reviews.\n\n6. **Technical Support**: Issues with getting adequate technical support or experiencing long troubleshooting processes can frustrate customers.\n\n7. **Value for Money**: There's often a discussion about whether customers feel they are getting what they pay for in terms of speed, service quality, and overall experience.\n\nTo get the latest and most specific reviews and complaints about Big V Telecom, checking customer feedback on platforms like Trustpilot, Google Reviews, and social media pages, or consumer complaint websites can provide more insight. Additionally, forums and community boards related to telecom service discussions can be a resource for real-life experiences from current and former customers.",
